void ll_open_cleanup ( struct super_block *  sb,
struct ptlrpc_request *  open_req 
)

Cleanup the open handle that is cached on MDT-side.

For open case, the client side open handling thread may hit error after the MDT grant the open. Under such case, the client should send close RPC to the MDT as cleanup; otherwise, the open handle on the MDT will be leaked there until the client umount or evicted.

In further, if someone unlinked the file, because the open handle holds the reference on such file/object, then it will block the subsequent threads that want to locate such object via FID.

Parameters:
[in] sb super block for this file-system
[in] open_req pointer to the original open request
